# ============================================================
# HISTORY CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: history
scope: history.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for history.

## policy_rules
History policy constrains:
- what historical material may be retained
- who may reference which historical material
- which reconstructions are permitted
- how historical detail may be disclosed
- when historical paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- retention scope must be explicit
- reference scope must be explicit
- reconstruction scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- bounded historical summary
- actor-scoped historical detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- restricted/archived historical detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow reference only for valid historical scope
- allow reconstruction only for explicit mode
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny current/historical overwrite
- deny hidden widening of reconstruction meaning

## escalation_rules
If historical basis,
reconstruction scope,
reference mode,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the history path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- retention policy is explicit
- reconstruction policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
